8. d3 { Defending the Bishop and threatening to trap the enemy Queen with c3. }
8... d6 { Attacking our Queen, trying to get some trades in. } 9. Qh4
{ Threatening to trap the enemy Queen with Pc3. } 9... Bxh3
{ Is a way for Black to simplify the position a bit, but his problems are not going anywhere after: }
10. Qxh3 { Threatening to simply play Rf1 and the enemy King is in trouble. }
10... Qf2 11. Bd2
{ This is really important in order to avoid ...Na5 ideas while also threatening to play Be1 trapping the enemy Queen! }
11... Nd4 12. c3 { Getting rid of Black's only active piece. } 12... Ne6 13.
Kc2
{ White's King is really safe on c2 and we can continue with Rhf1 and the enemy Queen is running out of squares. }
