10. a4
{ Played by former World Junior Champion, Lu Shanglei, with the idea to meet ... Nd7 with g4! }
10... Nd7
{ Threatening to push ...f5 while also introducing ...Bg5 ideas. This plan works really well when White castles short, but here you see why we postponed it: }
11. g4
{ Simply stopping Black's ...f5 break! Now you may be wondering where do we castle? The answer to that question is, we go Queen-Side! }
11... Bg5 { This remains Black's only idea, but White has an easy game after: }
12. Be3 *

