5... O-O 6. Nf3
{ The most natural, and the best move in the position. Now this opens a door for Black to play ...Ng4 but generally you need to know that White is fine after playing Qe2! }
6... Ng4
{ Threatening to play ...Nf2, this is the only move that has some independent value as 6...Pd6 would transpose back to the main lines. }
7. Qe2
{ With the idea to meet ...Nf2 with the simple and strong Rf1! We are ready to kick the knight with h3 on the next move, so I think that is all you need to know for starters! But of course, make sure to check out the main course for more details about this position. }
