7... Be6
{ The most principled and by far the most popular move for Black, and one of the main tabias of the Vienna Game! Here I want you to remember the following combo: }
8. Bxd5
{ If you read my courses you know how much I am against giving up the Bishop Pair if not needed, but White has a very cool plan: }
8... Bxd5 9. f4
{ This is the modern concept of playing the Vienna Game! Now Black has a choice: }
9... exf4 { Is already really bad for Black after: } 10. Nxf4
{ Putting pressure on the Bd5. Black has to play: } 10... Bxc3 11. bxc3 O-O
{ But now White can grab the initiative after the typical Queen move: } 12. Qh5
{ Increasing the pressure over the Bd5. Please notice that ...Ne7 runs into Ba3! ideas. }
12... f5 13. Ba3 { Another unplesant move for Black to face. } 13... Rf6 14.
Rae1 { Threatening Nxd5 and Re8+ next, White is dominating the e file. } *

