5... Bg4
{ The most popular move, pinning the knight and preparing to continue with ...e6 followed by ...Be7 and ...O-O }
6. Nc3 e6 7. Be2
{ The ideal square for the light-squared bishop in this structure. Notice that Bd3 would weaken the d4-pawn! }
7... c6 { Preparing to play with ...Bd6!? } 8. O-O Bd6 9. h3
{ Forcing Black to show his hand. Most of the time black will answer with ...Bh5 because taking on f3 gives White a free edge thanks to the bishop pair. }
9... Bh5 10. Ne5
{ The most precise! Getting rid of the pin and activating the knight. } 10...
Bxe2 11. Qxe2 Nbd7 12. Bf4 { Strengthening the e5-knight. } 12... Qc7 13. Rad1
O-O 14. g4 { With Bg3 and f4 next, White is much better. } *

