3... Nf6 4. d3 Bb4
{ This is one of the most principled ways for Black to counter White's set-up. The point is to strike in the center with ...d5 on the next move. Objectively speaking, Black should be fine, but the positions are fresh, and generally, White has easier play, at least in my humble opinion. As a side note, a lot of people might play this variation trying to follow Sethuraman's 1... e5 Lifetime Repertoire, so we need to be well prepared against it! }
5. Ne2 { Reinforcing the c3-Knight and preparing O-O. } 5... d6
{ Is a playable line for Black, but simply inferior compared to the main  5...d5  push. The b4-Bishop is slightly misplaced now since White can always recapture with the Knight on c3 and keep a healthy pawn structure. Nevertheless, you should not relax yet because White's position is only slightly more pleasant and far from anything clear yet. }
6. O-O
{ Threatening to play the deadly combo with Bg5 and Nd5. Black has a few ways to react now: }
6... O-O { Natural, but careless. } 7. Bg5 { Threatening the lethal Nd5 next. }
7... h6
{ Is always the first thing that you want to ask yourself when playing/facing this kind of move pinning the Knight. The good news is that White can take direct actions with: }
8. Bxf6
{ Forcing Black's Queen to f6 so we can gain a tempo when playing Nd5! } 8...
Qxf6 9. Nd5
{ Hitting a number of things! The most important to point out are the enemy Queen and the c7-pawn, so Black has to go for the sad retreat. }
9... Qd8 10. c3
{ Keep in mind that this small move becomes available once the Knight has left the c3-square! By playing c3, White is harassing the enemy Bishop while also preparing to gain space on the Queenside with b4 and a4. }
10... Ba5 11. a4
{ I like this order even better than starting with the direct b4! Now White is threatening to trap the enemy Bishop with b4 and a5. }
11... Bb6 { Preparing to meet b4 with a5. } 12. Kh1
{ From several ways to be better, I like this one the most! White is simply preparing the thematic f4-push next with good play on the Kingside thanks to the strong Knight on d5. }
