10... Qf6
{ This is a very natural way for Black to react, with the idea to play ...Qg6 next, trying to get rid of the annoying White Queen. }
11. Ne4 { We stick to the plan, and we don't fear the endgame! } 11... Qg6
{ Trying to minimize the damage, but White gets a small but steady edge in the following endgame: }
12. Qxg6
{ Avoiding the endgame would have been a big loss of time, and instead, we are going for a slightly better endgame thanks to the Bishop pair. }
12... hxg6 13. f4 exf4 { Would be what White wants to see after: } 14. Nxd6
{ Eliminating the enemy dark-squared Bishop so we can recapture on f4 next, without allowing a Bishop trade! }
14... cxd6 15. Bxf4 { Putting pressure on the isolated d6-pawn. } 15... Ne5 16.
Bd5 { And the Bishop pair is shining. } *

