{ Staying very flexible, not committing to castling, yet!   10.O-O  Gave Black an interesting game after:  10...Rg8∞  With attacking chances for Black. }
10... O-O-O 11. Be3 { Hitting the a7-pawn. } 11... Kb8 12. f4
{ Black's position is a bit cramped now that there is no obvious plan for him. }
12... exf4 13. Nxf4 Rhe8
{ And here castling long would be the safer choice for White, but I prefer: }
14. O-O
{ Because there is no attack for Black on the Kingside, and we can attack with a4 and Nb5. }
