{ We don't mind playing with the isolated pawn since we can use the d-file for our Rook and also push e5 and play Ne4 at the right time. }
12... c6 13. h3
{ With a lot of ways for White to improve, for example, Rd1, Kh1 and Bh2 are very natural at first glance, and then White can start more concrete actions based on e5 and Ne4, while for Black it is not clear at all what to do despite having a solid position. }
