11... Qg6 { Hitting both the e4-pawn and the g2-pawn. } 12. O-O
{ This is the key move of the line! We give up the vital e4-pawn for an insane amount of compensation. Big shout out to Lc0 for coming up with this approach! }
12... Bh3
{ You would be surprised to see how many people fell for this already in my blitz games! Black is threatening mate, but White wins after: }
13. Nf4
{ Defending against the checkmate threat on g2 and winning the h3-Bishop. } *

