7. Nf3 exf4 8. Bxf4 { Threatening to push d4. } 8... Nd4 9. Qd2
{ This is a small improvement over the Damjanovic,V @@StartBracket@@2440@@EndBracket@@-Vajda,L @@StartBracket@@2370@@EndBracket@@ Bucharest 1996 game that we have in this line. The point is to play for O-O-O next withan improved version of the 5... exf4 lines because the inclusion of h3 and h5 favors White, as Black will have a hard time castling short. }
