7. Ng5
{ This is the trick! White is hitting the f7-square, and Black is not in time with the Nf2 business. }
7... O-O
{ This way Black is trying to accept his mistake and play a normal game, but White grabs the initiative after: }
8. f5 { Hitting the g4-Knight. } 8... Bf2+
{ Black can force a few trades, but White keeps a lot of pressure after: } 9.
Kf1 Ne3+ 10. Bxe3 Bxe3
{ And now the g5-Knight is hanging. Here you need to remember the key move to be ambitious as White: }
11. h4 { Temporarily sacrificing a pawn for initiative and threatening Qh5! }
11... Bxg5 12. hxg5 Qxg5 { More or less forced for Black to stay in the game. }
13. Rh5 Qd8 { The passive retreat is not better after: } 14. Kf2
{ Threatening both the direct Rxh7 and the simple Qg4 followed by Rah1. } *

