7... Na5 { Hunting the light-squared Bishop. } 8. Bg5
{ Threatening Nd5, ruining Black's pawn structure on the Kingside. } 8... c6
{ Controlling the d5-square. } 9. a3
{ With the idea to play Ba2 and save the light-squared Bishop. Black can no longer postpone his decision and has to go for: }
9... Nxc4 10. dxc4 { Threatening to take space on the Queenside with b4! }
10... a5 11. Qd3 { Preparing to castle long. } 11... h6 12. Bxf6 Qxf6 13. O-O-O
{ With a nice initiative for White on the Kingside, who will continue with g4 and h4, and then strike with g5 taking advantage of the h6-hook. }
