{ Black's most popular move in online chess! The idea is to increase the pressure on the f3-Knight and threaten to push ...b5 in some variations. We have to get rid of that d4-Knight immediately! }
8. Nxc5 { Eliminating the dark-squared Bishop. } 8... dxc5 9. c3
{ Getting rid of the annoying d4-Knight. } 9... Bxf3
{ Is a bit better because it's not losing the e5-pawn, but White keeps a comfortable position. }
10. gxf3 Nc6 11. Bb5 { Pinning the Knight and threatening fxe5! } 11... Nh5
{ With a little ....Qh4+ check in mind, but it shouldn't stop us from capturing the pawn: }
12. fxe5 Qh4+ 13. Ke2 { And White's king is nicely protected by the pawns. }
