{ Played in the correspondence game with the idea to develop the dark-squared Bishop to c5. }
13. Nf3 Bc5
{ Making it hard for us to castle short, but can go for the endgame by playing: }
14. Bxc5 Qxc5 15. Qf2
{ Ready for the endgame, and if Black avoids it, we can continue with O-O and then try to win the c3-pawn. }
15... Qxf2+ 16. Kxf2
{ With a balanced endgame for correspondence chess, but slightly easier to play for White in a human game because of the structural advantage. White can eliminate the c3-pawn by playing a4 followed by Ra3-Rxc3. Then he could look to open up the other side of the board with h4-h5. The game was eventually drawn in: ½-½ Eintalu,J @@StartBracket@@2358@@EndBracket@@-Tonisson,P @@StartBracket@@2401@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2018 }
