{ With a level game according to the computer, but with easier play for White from a practical perspective. I feel like White's moves are much easier to make. Play a4-Rab1, collect the c3-pawn, and then we can consider maneuvering the Knight around with something like Ne2-Nf4/Nd4. It just feels a bit easier to play. }
