{ The point of having played 3... d5! Black gets the e4-square for his Knight and solves the first problem. Black has some annoying ...Qh4+ ideas that we have to deal with now. The most natural way to block the check is to play the old main line with  5.Nf3  , but I am not a big fan of it because I feel like Black has plenty of ways to get a playable position. Therefore I recommend we try the more venomous and modern main line by playing: }
