5... Be6
{ This is a very interesting pawn sacrifice that was never tried, but I thought it's useful to at least be aware of it. }
6. Nxe4 dxe4 7. Qxe4 Bd5 8. Qf4
{ The safest square for the Queen, preparing to push d4 next. } 8... Nc6 9. d4
Nb4
{ The big point behind Black's play. Now we are forced to defend the pawn with the King: }
10. Kd1
{ With c3 next, I feel like White has good play with the strong pawn center despite losing the right to castle. I think this is already more than you need to know against this line. As I said, it's a novelty, and we need to see some games with it. }
