5... Nxc3 6. dxc3 Qh4+
{ @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/ppp2ppp/8/3pP3/4n3/2N2Q2/PPPP2PP/R1B1KBNR b KQkq - 1 5@@EndFEN@@ This is a way for Black to ''bail out'' and force the Queens off with ...Qe4+ on the next move. We have seena similar pattern in the  5...Nc6  line, followed by the same  6.--  Nxc3  and  7.--  Qh4+  , so this is a pretty thematic endgame that you need to be aware of. In this particular case, I think it's even a better version for White compared to what we've previously seen because the light-squared Bishop is not yet committed to  b5  and can be used to attack the e4-pawn. }
