9... Bf5 10. Ne2 Nc6 { Attacking the e5-pawn. } 11. Nd4
{ A nice counterattack putting pressure on the f5-Bishop! } 11... Bg6 12. h4
{ Threatening to trap the Bishop with h5, in case Black goes for the bait with ...Nxe5. }
12... O-O-O 13. h5
{ Almost trapping the Bishop! Black can escape by improving our pawn structure: }
