{ This is the standard set-up for White, so you may want to take a mental screenshot here because this is how you want to arrange your pieces when Black plays to castle short. }
12... Nc5 { Threatening to eliminate our light-squared Bishop with ...Nxd3! }
13. Bf5 { Threatening to increase the pressure with Qg4 next. } 13... g6
{ May look a bit scary but keep in mind that you can play: } 14. g4
{ And the f5-Bishop can't be captured because of gxf5, and you can continue with pushing the h-pawn down the board. }
