5... e6
{ Planning to fianchetto the light-squared Bishop by playing ...b6 and ...Bb7, but this allows White to develop the Bishop to d3! }
6. Nc3 Be7 7. Bd3
{ Because there is no pressure on the f3-Knight now, we can develop the Bishop on the most active square! }
7... O-O 8. O-O c5 { Can be met with the simple: } 9. dxc5 Bxc5 10. Qe2
{ Preparing to play Bf4 followed by Rad1. } 10... Nc6 11. Bf4
{ With Rad1 next, White can consider plans such as advancing the Queenside pawns with a3-b4, or to set-up the battery by playing Bb1 followed by Qc2-Bg5 ideas. }
