13. Bg4+
{ This is a nice check to add in, as the direct Rd2 could have been met by ...Be6, leading to a complicated game. }
13... Kb8 14. Rd2
{ With Rhd1 and b3-Bb2 followed by c4-ideas, White is enjoying a risk free advantage. Alekseev,E @@StartBracket@@2642@@EndBracket@@-Milanovic,D @@StartBracket@@2469@@EndBracket@@ Berlin 2015 }
