{ Black's main move, putting pressure in the center and preparing O-O-O. } 5.
Nc3 { Setting up a trap because White gets a big edge after  5...Bxf3? } 5...
Qh5
{ This is Black's most popular move and, objectively speaking, the best line. To understand why I like White's position, we can now compare it with the 3. Nf3 lines where we would have the same position, but instead of the c3-Knight, there will be a Bishop on e2. This small nuance gives Black enough time to go for ...O-O-O and ...e5 counterplay, which I find utterly annoying. Now the point of having played Nc3 is that we get an additional option to play: }
