{ Preparing to defend the d4-pawn with c3! } 10... O-O-O
{ Threatening ...Rxd4! } 11. c3
{ Covering the d4-pawn and waiting to see how Black is planning to develop so we can react accordingly. }
11... Be7 { Trying to avoid the Bg5-ideas. } 12. Ke2
