{ Forced because  11.Bxf3  allows  ...Nxc4!  It's easy to forget about the c4-pawn if you are not used to the Alekhine structure. }
11... Qh4+ 12. Bf2
{ No need to panic! Now Black has two plans:  •  12...Qh3  @@StartBracket@@stopping White from castling short@@EndBracket@@  •  12...Qf4  @@StartBracket@@keeping an eye on the d4-pawn@@EndBracket@@ }
12... Qh3
{ This move is rarely seen compared to  12...Qf4  , but some people might go for it. }
13. c5
{ Kicking the b6-Knight, with the idea to play Qb3 next and gain a tempo by attacking the b7-pawn. }
13... Nd7 14. Qb3 { Hitting the b7-pawn. } 14... O-O-O 15. O-O-O
{ We play Ne4 next, with a comfortable edge for White, as our pawn center restricts Black's pieces. }
