Be7 { The main move in both OTB and online chess. } 10. Be2
{ 10.d5  is also possible in this position and was tried by a lot of people. I just feel like going for Be2 might be easier since it requires less dynamic play, and White has a solid positional edge. }
10... O-O 11. O-O
{ And now Black has a variety of plans. Most people tend to break in the center with  11...f6  ,  whichtransposes to the 5... Bf5 and 8... Be7 move order. }
11... Bg4 12. Qd2 { Preparing to bring the Rook with Rad1. } 12... f6 13. exf6
Bxf6 14. Rad1
{ With Ne4 coming on the next move, White has a solid advantage. Keep in mind that ...Bxf3 is always answered by Rxf3! because the natural Bxf3 allows ...Nxc4! and you don't want to see that. }
