1. e4 Nc6
{ The Nimzowitsch Defense. Named after Aron Nimzowitsch, who was a Latvian-born Danish chess player and writer. He was the foremost figure amongst the hypermodern and wrote a very influential book on chess theory ''My System''. In the late 1920s, he was one of the best chess players in the world. }
2. d4 e5 { A solid line favored by the late British grandmaster Tony Miles. }
3. dxe5 Nxe5 4. Nf3 { Developing with tempo. } 4... Qf6 5. Nc3
{ Threatening Nd5. } 5... Nxf3+ 6. Qxf3 Qxf3 7. gxf3
{ We simply got the Scotch endgame where normally Black would have an extra Bc5-move on the board, so this is definitely an improved version for White. }
7... c6 8. Rg1 { Activating the Rook. } 8... Ne7 9. Be3
{ We are going to castle long next, while Black is struggling to finish his development. White went on to win in: So,W @@StartBracket@@2770@@EndBracket@@-Vachier Lagrave,M @@StartBracket@@2778@@EndBracket@@ Lichess.org INT 2020 }
