5. Bd2
{ There is no need to play c3 when we can just gain a small lead in development. }
5... Nxf3+ 6. Qxf3 Bxd2+ 7. Nxd2 { Preparing to castle long next. } 7... d6 8.
O-O-O Nf6 { Threatening ...Bg4! } 9. h3
{ We are ready to push on the Kingside with g4-g5 followed by pushing the h-pawn, with a steady initiative. }
