{ The Owen Defense. The opening is named after the English vicar and strong 19th-century amateur chess player John Owen, an early exponent. Using his opening, Owen defeated Paul Morphy in an informal game in London, 1858. }
2. d4 Ba6
{ The Guatemala Defense. There is not much that you need to know against this variation. Just play: }
3. Bxa6 { Forcing Black's Knight on a pretty awkward square. } 3... Nxa6 4. Nf3
{ We can castle short next with a much better position thanks to the extra space. }
