{ This is usually the type of move that the lower-rated players are making. At first, it looks like an active move, but they don't think about the long-term consequences. In this case, White will sidestep with Bc2, and then what this move did, it simply surrendered the central tension. White can choose to either play on the Kingside or on the Queenside with b3. }
7. Bc2
{ Simply sidestepping Black's threat while keeping the e4-pawn well defended. }
7... Nf6 { Threatening ...Nxe4. } 8. Re1
