1. e4 a6
{ The St. George Defense! This opening is giving White a free edge because it's not influencing the center in any way. It became famous after Tony Miles used it to beat the reigning World Champion Anatoly Karpov at the European Team Championship in Skara in 1980. }
2. d4 b5 { Preparing to play ...Bb7 ➼ attacking the e4-pawn. } 3. Nf3
{ Developing the Knight on the natural square. Keep in mind that this move can be made automatically, while we are less happy about going Nc3 because of a potential ...b4-move that could be annoying. }
3... Bb7 { Hitting the e4-pawn. } 4. Bd3
{ Simply defending the pawn and preparing a short castle. Now Black can choose from two different plans:  •  4...e6  @@StartBracket@@the cautious move@@EndBracket@@  •  4...Nf6  @@StartBracket@@the aggressive approach@@EndBracket@@ }
4... e6 { Preparing to push ...c5, this is Black's best plan. } 5. O-O c5
{ Threatening to play ...cxd4 and get a Paulsen type of Sicilian, or even ...c4 in some positions with the idea that the e4-pawn could become vulnerable. }
6. c3
{ Of course, we will not allow Black to get rid of our nice pawn center easily. We are ready to recapture with the pawn on d4 and keep our nice space advantage. }
6... Nf6 { Threatening ...Nxe4! } 7. Re1
{ Defending the e4-pawn and activating the Rook. } 7... d6
{ 7...cxd4  Is going to end uptransposing to the 6... cxd4 lines. } 8. a4
{ Forcing Black to make an ugly move on the Queenside. } 8... c4
{ The most natural reaction, but White has a clever trick to undermine the Queenside: }
9. Bc2 { Sidestepping Black's theatre and keeping the e4-pawn well defended. }
9... Nbd7 10. b3
{ This move might come as a shocker to a lot of people because the e4-pawn needs protection from the c2 Bishop. But who said we are going to recapture on b3 immediately? }
10... cxb3 11. Bd3
{ The point! Bxb3 would have allowed Black to take on e4, so we are preparing to recapture on b3 with the Queen, this way keeping our central pawn well defended. }
11... Be7 12. Qxb3 { And the Black Queenside is shaky. } *

